@node rx_loadmodule "ARexx Loadmodule"

    (¯`·._.·' Showmodule GUI Mega Webber `·._.·'¯)


           (_.·'¯ AREXX / Loadmodule ¯`·._)

             Load a module into the program

    @{b}LOADMODULE@{ub} module [anchor]

        Arguments:
            · module
                This is the modulename.
                Aliases can be used.
                If any spaces in the name,
                please use quotes.

            · anchor
                An optional agrument.
                If you wish to start at a
                special anchor in the module.


        EXAMPLE:
            Let's load dos/dos.m, and go to the
            datestamp object.

            @{fg shine}'LOADMODULE dos/dos "OBJECT datestamp"'@{fg text}

        RETURNS
            RC=0 if success
            RC=1 if failure
@endnode
@node rx_save "ARexx Save"

    (¯`·._.·' Showmodule GUI Mega Webber `·._.·'¯)


              (_.·'¯ AREXX / Save ¯`·._)

                    Save management

    @{b}SAVE@{ub} mode [filename] [FORCE]

        Arguments:
            · mode
              This could be either
              o @{b}TEXT@{ub} to save plain text or
              o @{b}AMIGAGUIDE@{ub} to save as a amigaguide document.
              o @{b}OPEN@{ub} to open the Save window
              o @{b}CLOSE@{ub} to close the save window

            · filename
              This is the name you wish to save it as.
              If leaved out; a filerequester will ask
              you for the path.

            · FORCE
              If this argument is used, you will not be able
              to confirm overwriting files.

        RETURNS
            RC=0 if success
            RC=1 if failure
