@node wnd_links "Edit Links window"

    (¯`·._.·' Showmodule GUI Mega Webber `·._.·'¯)


             (_.·'¯ Edit Links window ¯`·._)


This is the links part; the reason for why the program
is partially named "Webber".

When you click a node in the anchor contents (right listview)
in the @{"main" link wnd_main} window, smgmw will compare the
choosen node with the link patterns. If they match, smgmw will
load the module the node is linked to and jump to the choosen
anchor.

Gadgets:
    @{b} Listview @{ub}
        Contains the link patterns.

    @{bg shine}  Add   @{bg back}
        Add a link

    @{bg shine} Remove @{bg back}
        Remove the selected link from the list

    @{bg shine}   Up   @{bg back}
        Moves the selected link one step up

    @{bg shine}  Down  @{bg back}
        Moves the selected link one step down


    @{b} Pattern @{ub}
        The pattern of the link. Amiga DOS Wildcards are supported.

    @{b} Module @{ub}
        The module smgmw should load if the pattern match.
        You can use @{"aliases" link wnd_edhots}if you like.

    @{b} Anchor @{ub}
        The name of the anchor that should be viewed when
        the module has been loaded.
            For example: OBJECT window
@endnode

